ceph-menv

Installation

1. Build links

# assuming ceph build directory is at $HOME/build/ceph
$ cd ceph-mtools
$ sh ./build_links.sh


2. Add alias

To your shell startup script (such as $HOME/.bashrc) add:

alias mset='source ~/ceph-menv/mset.sh'

3. Modify PATH

Add path to ceph-menv/bin to PATH. It should precede any reference to $HOME/ceph/build/bin path.

4. Modify PS1:

Add references to $MRUN_PROMPT and potentially $MRUN_PROMPT_COLOR in PS1, for example:

case "$TERM" in
xterm-*color)
    PS1='${debian_chroot:+($debian_chroot)}\[\033[$MRUN_PROMPT_COLOR;1m\]${MRUN_PROMPT}\[\033[01;32m\]\u@\h\[\033[00m\]:\[\033[01;34m\]\w\[\033[00m\]\$ '
    ;;
*)
    PS1='${debian_chroot:+($debian_chroot)}${MRUN_PROMPT}\u@\h:\w\$ '
    ;;
esac


